"# Evaluating and Adapting the Measures Already Implemented\nThe set of measures already being implemented, adapted to the problem and the urgency of the epidemic, constitutes a kind of surveillance system in itself, particularly in terms of organization. # Early-Warning Systems\nEarly-warning systems (EWSs) are a variant of surveillance systems, designed to anticipate a disaster and limit its effects. There is a tendency to confuse EWSs and the use of space technology (satellite photos)."